g, and horseback riding. The presence of first-rate lodging options in Panchgani is one of the key factors contributing to a relaxing trip. Families, couples, and groups of friends may all find hotels in Panchgani that are both luxurious and affordable. These hotels provide incredible facilities, including thrilling outdoor sports, and are well-equipped with the latest conveniences. Additionally, this location offers a variety of eco-friendly camping options, as well as the chance to camp out at night. So, no matter what sort of tourist you are, pack your bags and head to Panchgani to enjoy a luxurious vacation filled with history, adventure, nature, and much more. 9. Tapola It is one of the greatest spots to visit in Mahabaleshwar. Tapola is a little town known for the stunning Shivsagar lake, and it is sometimes referred to as the "Mini Kashmir" of the west. Tourists enjoy activities such as swimming in the lake and riding a water scooter, kayaking, or taking a motorboat trip. For the unforgettable view, wait till sunset. Trekking in the Tapola forests is another option for adventurers. The nearby strawberry fields are a must-see while visiting. 10. Elphinstone Point Murray discovered Elphinstone Point in the year 1830. It is among the highest points in Mahabaleshwar. Mount Stuart Elphinstone, the legislative head of the Bombay Administration at the time, inspired the naming of the Elphinstone Point. Elphinstone Point is one of the most beautiful places in Mahabaleshwar, and the gorgeous surroundings add to its beauty. When one reaches the peak, one might wonder about the magnificent view of the Pratapgarh Stronghold, the Koyna Valley, and nearby farmland. The valley between Elphinstone Point and Arthur's Seat Point also deserves recognition, and it is the starting point of Savitri Stream. Address: 402303 Elphinstone Point, Mahabaleshwar, Satara, Maharashtra. Timing: 9 am to 6 pm Entry fee: Entry is free 11. Pratapgad Fort Maharashtra's Pratapgad is a hill fort. T