ss the sun setting behind Sahyadri Mountain. Tourists can see a panoramic image of Pratapgarh fort, which is encircled by the Kova valley on one side and the Savitri valley on the other. Address: 402303 Satara, Maharashtra Timing: Timings are from 6 am to 7 pm Entry fee: Free 2. Chinaman's Falls One of the most well-known attractions to visit in Mahabaleshwar is the Chinaman's Falls, which is about 2.5 km south of the city in the Koyana valley. Since the Chinese were responsible for maintaining the surrounding gardens, therefore waterfall is known as Chinaman's waterfall. As sunlight passes through the falls, that time the water shimmers like gold and diamonds. The beautiful surroundings, stunning waterfalls, and gardens make it a perfect vacation destination. It is the ideal destination for a holiday that offers a stunning experience. Arrange a picnic at Chinaman's falls for you and your loved ones. The monsoon season is the best time to view the falls. It is one of the favourite areas to visit in Mahabaleshwar because of its peaceful surroundings. If you visit Mahabaleshwar, you should visit Chinaman Falls. The time requires to visit and see Chinaman's falls is 2 or 3 hours. Address: 412806 Mahabaleshwar, Maharashtra Timing: All day Entry fee: Entry is free 3. Dhobi Waterfall It is one of Mahabaleshwar's best tourist destinations. Dhobi falls are a collection of waterfalls that connect Elphinston Point and Lodwick, and after that, connect Petit Road to Old Mahabaleshwar Road. The Dhobi waterfall is located around 3 kilometres from Mahabaleshwar's main town. For adventure lovers and picnickers, a waterfall has always been a particularly attractive destination. One of the greatest spots to visit in Mahabaleshwar is the Koyna River; it is a tributary of the Krishna River that falls directly into the valley from the mountains. Visitors can spend the day in this place that is encircled by the waterfall, greenery, rocks and natural beauty to avoid dullness. Therefore, a